| {{circa|lk=no}} 1440 || [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]] || ''[[Quốc âm thi tập]]''<ref>{{cite book | title = Culture and customs of Vietnam | first1 = Mark W. | last1 = MacLeod | first2 = Thi Dieu| last2 = Nguyen | publisher = Greenwood Publishing Group | year = 2001 | isbn = 978-0-313-30485-9 | page = 68 }}</ref> || Isolated names in [[Chữ nôm]] date from the early 13th century.
|-
| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1462 || [[Albanian language|Albanian]] || ''Formula e Pagëzimit'', a baptismal formula in a letter of Archbishop [[Pal Engjëlli|Pal Engjëll]] || Some scholars interpret a few lines in the ''[[Bellifortis]]'' text (1405) as Albanian.<ref>{{cite journal | first = Robert | last = Elsie | author-link = Robert Elsie | title = The Bellifortis Text and Early Albanian | journal = Zeitschrift für Balkanologie | volume = 22 | number = 2 | year = 1986 | pages = 158–162 | url = http://www.elsie.de/pdf/articles/A1986Bellifortis.pdf }}</ref>
|-
| {{circa|lk=no}} 1470 || [[Finnish language|Finnish]] || single sentence in a German travel journal<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wulff|first=Christine|title=Zwei Finnische Sätze aus dem 15. Jahrhundert|journal=Ural-Altaische Jahrbücher NF Bd. 2|language=German|pages=90–98}}</ref> || The first printed book in Finnish is ''[[Abckiria]]'' (1543) by [[Mikael Agricola]].
|-
| {{circa|lk=no}} 1470 || [[Maltese language|Maltese]] || ''[[Il Cantilena]]'' ||
|-
| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1485 || [[Yi language|Yi]] || bronze bell inscription in [[Dafang County]], [[Guizhou]]<ref>{{cite book | title = Language Policy in the People's Republic of China: Theory and Practice since 1949 | editor1-first = Minglang | editor1-last = Zhou | editor2-first = Hongkai | editor2-last = Sun | publisher = Springer | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-1-4020-8038-8 | page = 258 }}</ref> ||
