| {{circa|lk=no}}&nbsp;1550 || [[Standard Dutch]] || ''[[Statenbijbel]]'' || The ''Statenbijbel'' is commonly accepted to be the start of Standard Dutch, but various experiments were performed around 1550 in Flanders and Brabant. Although none proved to be lasting they did create a semi-standard and many formed the base for the ''Statenbijbel''.
